{
  "texts": [
    "In this work, we developed a novel attention-based transformer model for the task of heart disease prediction.",
    "This model applied the strength of position-level attention mechanisms and self-attention layers to learn the representation of the complete sequence, in contrast to conventional RNN methods.",
    "Through the use of this distinct mechanism, we were able to identify and evaluate the relative weights of the various sequence components, improving the effectiveness of prediction.",
    "Beyond heart disease, a variety of clinical risk prediction tasks can be performed using the proposed technique due to its versatility.",
    "The fundamental advantage of this architecture is its well-designed network topology, which enables maximum parallelization."
  ]
}